{"id":448060160,"question_id":583,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"4 years, 1 month","timestamp":1611665938,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"584 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/448060160/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Delete Operation for Two Strings","memory":"18.3 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def minDistance(self, s: str, t: str) -> int:\n        dp = [[-1 for i in range(len(t))] for j in range(len(s))]\n        def helper(s, t, i, j):\n            temp = \"\"\n            if i == len(s):\n                return \"\"\n            if j == len(t):\n                return \"\"\n            if dp[i][j] != -1:\n                return dp[i][j]\n            if s[i] == t[j]:\n                temp = s[i] + helper(s, t, i+1, j+1 )\n                return temp\n\n            f = helper(s, t, i+1, j )\n            s = helper(s, t, i, j+1 )\n            minm = max(len(temp), len(f), len(s))\n            if minm == len(temp):\n                dp[i][j] = temp\n                return temp\n            if minm == len(f):\n                dp[i][j] = f\n                return f\n            dp[i][j] = s\n            return s\n        lcs = helper(s, t, 0, 0)\n        return len(s) + len(t) - 2 * len(lcs)","compare_result":"","title_slug":"delete-operation-for-two-strings","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
